		<div class="mx-auto diagonal-section-content">
			<h1>About</h1>
			<div class="container">
				The OSU/BH Hackathon is a 24-hour energy-forward / sustainability/ green hackathon organised by Oklahoma State University and Baker Hughes.
				The hackathon will see students come together to build an innovative hack to help with energy transition.
				<br/><br/>
							
				Hackers will be a combination of students across any majors, but we expect most with majors related to computer science, environmental engineering, electrical engineering, and mechanical engineering.
				<br/><br/>
							
				The hacks can be pure software, electrical, mechanical... or maybe even a combindation!
							
				<br/><br/>
				Naturally, there will be free food, some freebies,and the chance to gain prizes and meet our incredible sponsors, don’t hesitate to apply.
			</div>
